inn1.comm: Beauty to start off the proceedings. It landed on a length, on the middle stump line before it went across Butt who pushes tentatively and is beaten
full and outside off and this time Butt lets it go through
Further outside off and Butt has no problems in leaving it. He swirls the bat over his shoulder as a warm-up exercise and gets ready to face the next ball

impressive start from the bowler. Again on the right line and the length, closer to the off stump and Butt is beaten again. Credit to him, though, he is pushing inside the line and not chasing the delivery
back to the outside off line and left alone
nice. On the middle and leg, Butt thinks about flicking it to leg side, the ball swings away and he checks his shot, pushes with a straight face and the ball runs away to the off side
full and down the leg side, tries to flick away but makes no contact
And again. Its a good delivery to the right hand batsman but not to the lefty. wide called.
much better - gets this one on the stumps and Nasir leans forward to defend

gets even better with a delivery pushed across Nasir who shapes to play at it before withdrawing it at the last minute. The bowler will think he has beaten the bat, the batsman will feel he was in control there
back to regular programming. Again drifting on that leg stump line and Nasir helps himself to a easy boundary to fine leg
on the off stump line and Nasir gets forward, bat and pad together and pushes it to the off side
lands on the leg and middle, moves towards middle and Nasir plays close to the body and turns it to the leg side.
Chigumbara catches the legside disease and Butt gets off the mark with a flick behind square leg
on the off stump line, full in length, and Nasir pushes it to covers
right on money again; on that off stump line, perfect length too and Nasir defends compactly.
similar line again and Nasir is emboldened to drive down the track but the bowler puts his right hand out to make the stop before threatening to throw it back at the stumps.
pushes this one across Nasir who lets the 'keeper come into play
fuller, just outside off stump and Nasir pushes - the feet didn't move forward this time and he gets an inside edge to the leg side
a touch short in length, just outside off stump and Butt punches it to the point region
some swing there. It starts early in the trajectory though and then seams away after landing on a length around off stump, Butt lets it go through to the 'keeper
beaten this time though. This one again swung across the batsman but this one pitched around the middle stump and Butt was sucked into a forward prod.
after an listless first over he is hitting the right areas now. Another one swinging away and since it starts from around off stump, Butt shoulders arms
pushed to point
nice variation. This one comes in after landing on the middle, not much pace to worry Butt though, and he adjusts by turning it to the leg side
length delivery that straightens after landing around middle and off and Nasir adjusts to the late movement by stopping the front foot movement and hurriedly defends
gets behind the line of a length delivery this time and pushes it to the off side
fuller and outside off stump, Nasir is drawn into a forward push and the ball rolls away to the off side
gets off the strike with a dab to wide third man
lands outside off stump and moves further away, easy decision for Butt to leave
closer to the off stump and bit of extra bounce too and Salman sways away from the line, pulling his bat behind him so that there is no danger of the ball clipping the outside edge
on the off stump line and Nasir pushes it to covers. He has a chat with the non-striker and is now ready to face the next one. On wide slip in place.
the tight line continues. No room or length to work with - on and around that off stump - and Nasir defends
deja-vu.
this one straightens a touch after landing on the middle and off stump and it runs off the inner half of the bat to the leg side
after an listless first over he is hitting the right areas now. Another one swinging away and since it starts from around off stump, Butt shoulders arms

another maiden over. Impressive start this. On that off stump line and all Nasir can do is to defend. Pakistan don't want to lose an early wicket and adopting a cautious approach. The ball is moving around a touch.
on the off stump line, defended to the off side
breaks free with a lovely extra cover drive. It was fullish, allowing Butt to drive without a worry and he bisects the gap in the off side. It was a caressed push.
angled across Butt who lets it go past him
just short of driveable length, and slanting away but Butt resists any urge to repeat that cover drive and shoulders arms
further outside off, again on that good length and Taibu, who gathers that one, is impressed with the delivery.
even outside off stump and Butt watches Taibu collect
on the off stump line, going across with the angle, Nasir pushes on the up and the ball is in the air but falls well short of covers
super delivery. Comprehensively beaten. It was fuller, starts from middle stump and moves in the air and Nasir is caught at the crease.
gets behind the line of this length delivery and turns it to point
on the off stump line, defended to the off side
starts in the air, outside leg, lands on leg stump line and moves towards middle and the batsman is forced to defend
short in length and Butt cuts to wide third man for a single
and there he goes. It was a full delivery, on the middle stump and Nasir tried to slog it over mid-on and the swing takes it over mid-off. Safe, though.
on the off stump line, run down to third man
Butt takes a step forward, the bowler drags back the length cleverly and he turns to the leg side. Pakistan are hinting at attack now.
a touch short in length, cutting across Butt who withdraws his bat from the line
and again.
angling away and Nasir tickles it to fine third man and will pick up couple of runs. The third man was standing wide
run-out missed! It was a full delivery, around off stump, driven towards extra cover and the fielder fires in a throw at non-strikers ends but he misses it.

huge appeal for a catch down leg side but a wide is called! OMG! There was a huge noise there. Pad atleast, definitely not a wide. Taibu flung himself to his right to take a spectacular 'catch' but a wide is called. The replays reveal it did hit the pad, not sure whether it got the bat before.
another risky run, pushed to point and they rush across for a quick single. Again, the throw is not accurate and the batsmen get home
a touch short and is cut to wide third man
Butt reprises Nasir's cut and will retain the strike
fullish, on the off stump line, driven straight to mid-off
cracking cut. It was not all that short and just outside off stump, Butt made room by arching back and cut it through point
full in length, on the off stump line and Butt drives to covers
whack. Fullish, outside off stump and Butt drills it uppishly, past the cover fielder who should have taken it but the ball seemed to swerve away from him. Bit late to react
on the pads, tickled to square leg, they think about a single but decide against it
outside off stump, glided past backward point for two runs.
on the off stump, holds its line a touch and Butt decides at the last minute to pull but doesn't get much power behind it and the ball rolls away to the midwicket
picks up a single with a dab past backward point
another dab to third man, another single
fullish, on the off stump, worked to backward point
on the off stump line and pushed to the off side
where did that come from? It was a full delivery, on the stumps, Nasir clears the front foot, bends down his back knee and just heaves it over long-on. Ala Abdul Razzaq.
full again, outside off stump, though, and Nasir opens the bat-face and runs it to backward point
beaten. Chigumbura dragged back the length a touch and pushed it across Nasir who was sucked into a forward prod.
another slap towards long-on but there is a fielder at the deep and he is restricted to a single.
confusion over a single but they recover in time. It was jabbed away to the leg side, Salman starts and Nasir rushes across. But Salman sends him back and Nasir makes it back in time.
a touch short and Nasir pulls it to wide long on for a single
lands on the leg stump line, on a length, cuts towards off and is pushed back to the bowler
knifed through the line. It was a length delivery, just outside off stump and Salman just hit through the line and over the bowler's head.
mishits a punchy drive and the ball heads towards mid-off
change of pace. Slower one, loopy and Butt picks it up and defends to the leg side.
110.7 kmph, on a length, on the stumps, punched through covers for a single
on the off stump, punched to covers

And what a time to post that comment?! Butt is gone, flashing to backward point. It was a length delivery, outside off stump and Butt tried to make his own length and went for a slash but  it flew straight to the fielder. Zimbabwe have broken through.
full and just outside off stump, coming in with the angle and Younis moves forward, waits for the ball to come to him and flicks it behind square leg.
full again and well outside off stump, Younis leaned forward to reach the pitch and drove pleasingly to the cover region
on a length this time, again outside off stump, Younis tries to run it down to third man, mistimes it towards gully and will pick up a single
on the off stump line, guided to point
quick single taken with a push towards point
on a length, on the middle and off, pushed to cover point
slower one, just 87.3 kmph, and is pulled to long-on
on the off stump line, pushed straight to covers where the fielder gets a bad bounce and gives away an run
one bounce over midwicket boundary. Not all that short, mind you, but Nasir pulls it crisply.
fullish, on the off stump line, driven to covers
shuffles towards off stump and square drives on the up to backward point
wide of off stump and Younis slashes it away uppishly. The point fielder dived to his left but couldn't reach it.
leans forward to a length delivery, opens the bat-face and works it to backward point
full and outside off stump, punched to deep point

dropped at long-on by Mupariwa. Nasir heaved a full delivery towards Mupariwa who backpedalled a short distance but couldn't hold on to the catch. Why was he standing inside the line in the first place? Hmm?
leans forward to defend

Strikes first ball. Caught dead plumb by the inswinger. It started to move in late from the off stump line and struck the front pad dead in front. Younis didn't expect the ball to come in the air and had pushed his front leg a touch across. Gone! Mupariwa, who dropped that catch, is singing the redemption song.
full in length, outside off stump and is left alone
probing delivery on the off stump, Yousuf takes care not to press his front leg across and defends.
on the off stump line, defended solidly to the off side
rolled his finger across the seam at release and the ball straightened as a result after landing on the off stump and Yousuf runs it down to third man
Hit high in the air, over the bowler's head, Srinivas Raju, our scorer, was screaming six! six! but gravity pulled it down and the ball just came to stop after landing inside the ropes.
beaten there. Full and well outside off stump and Yousuf went for a lazy waft. Chigumbura is bowling his tenth consecutive over.
beaten on the drive again. The front leg is not coming across as much - perhaps he is worried about the indipper and as a result he is playing away from the body.
moves towards the line this time to defend
short of length, outside off stump, Yousuf pushes, away from the body, to point
full and outside off, driven to covers. Can he bring the next on in?

he gets it to straighten again and is pushed to covers. Waqar Younis, on air, is impressed. "Axecellent over," he says. Chigumbura spell reads: 10-2-36-01. He started with a maiden and ended with one.
pulled straight to midwicket. It was a seam-up delivery, on the stumps and Nasir went for a pull, but only succeeded in sending it straight to the fielder
lovely inswinger - that seems to be his stock delivery. It starts late in the air and almost trapped Malik in front. Malik got his bat down in a hurry and jabs it off the inside-edge to the leg side
outside off stump and is pushed to covers
on the off stump line, defended to the off side
leans forward to defend back to the bowler.
outside off stump,  Malik goes back to defend down the track
floated on the leg stump line, Yousuf goes for a sweep, gets a bottom edge and it rolls away to the 'keeper down the leg side
picks up a single with a dab past square leg
slow through the air, on the middle and leg, Malik goes back to tickle it behind square leg
similar line and Yousuf too repeats that shot to get a single. Price needs to shift his line to middle
on the middle this time and Malik pushes it down the track
on the middle and off stump line, turns towards off, pushed to the off side
full and outside off stump, Yousuf drives pleasingly to left of mid-off where Brent makes a fine diving stop
now a fine stop by Debengwa at extra cover. Yousuf had driven to his right and Debengwa threw himself to his right
on a length now  - after two full deliveries- and is defended to backward point
further outside off stump and Yousuf chases it and square drives to point
full and on the off stump and is driven to long-off (the fielder had dropped back)
walks down the track, gets too close to a length delivery and can only push it back to the bowler

Run out! Malik is gone.  Yousuf had come down the track for a lofted shot but was beaten in the flight and the inside edge saved him from getting stumped but the damage was done in the other end. The ball had rolled to short fine leg where Willams swooped on the ball and acted on the confusion between the batsmen and threw in a direct hit at the non-striker's end. The Pakistan captain is gone. He was late in getting back too; almost as if he didn't expect the throw to come in at his end.
goes back to defend to the leg side
lands outside leg stump, turns in, Yousuf goes back to flick it past square leg
on the middle and leg, turned to the leg side
goes back to wrist it to square leg
leans forward to push a full delivery to mid-off
outside off, from a length, square driven to point
full and outside off, mistimes a drive to extra cover

The pressure works! Yousuf is caught and bowled! Sharp catch too. It was fullish and Yousuf drives powerfully to the left of Mupariwa who holds on to it. 66 for 1 has turned into 78 for 5. Enter Shahid Afridi.
Afridi has a slash off his first ball. A touch short in length, outside off stump and Afridi lashes it to deep point
on the middle, coming in a touch, worked to square leg
on the middle stump line, paddled to short fine leg
goes back to defend very cautiously to the off side
flighted up, slow through the air and Misbah leans forward to defend towards backward point
pulled away to the midwicket boundary. Again slow in the air and a touch short and Misbah pulled it to left of the midwicket fielder
fuller, nurdled to the right of midwicket for a quick single
tossed-up, on the off stump line and Afridi defends. I am not lying, he really did defend.
full and outside off, Misbah jabs at it, feet nowhere in line and gets an inside edge to fine leg
Afridi picks up his first boundary. He just walked across towards the off stump and with a packed off side field, he swung this full delivery to the midwicket boundary
on the off stump line and Afridi defends to the off side
lands on a length, on the off stump, cuts away a touch and Afridi drives to long-off
in the zone outside off and Misbah lets Taibu, standing up to the stumps, gather
outside off stump, pushed to point
Afridi charges out but adjusts to the length by defending
slightly short and Afridi goes back to cut it past point
goes back to turn it to backward square leg
Maximum! Misbah went down on his knee to heave a flighted delivery over long-on. Mighty strike. Great to watch too.
goes back to turn it to backward square leg
outside off stump and is pushed to covers
full and outside off, beaten on the drive
takes a step forward and drives to right of long-off
another heave, this time miscued drive over extra cover and he will pick up two more
fullish, just outside off stump, Afridi jabs at it and gets a outside edge to backward point
slightly short in length and Afridi cuts it fiercely to wide third man region for two runs
keeps the strike with a drive to long-on
on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
a touch short and Afridi slaps it to sweeper cover
on the off stump line and Misbah reverse sweeps it to short third man
goes back to whip it past square leg
a touch short and Misbah pulls it for a single
full in length, lands outside off stump and moves away, left alone. Taibu is standing up to the stumps
on the stumps, full, driven to mid-on
length delivery outside off stump and Misbah cuts it to backward point
leans forward to push a full delivery to covers
fuller, on the middle and leg, driven to long-on
on the leg and middle, turning in, defended to the leg side
goes back to tickle past square leg
There he goes. A dance down the track and a heave over long-on. The crowd roar their approval.
backs to the leg side, and glides to backward point

Interesting. Again, Afridi backs away, Price keeps his close and sends down a flighted delivery, slow in the air and is cut to deep point. Salim Malik used to do this a lot, moving outside leg stump to the spinners.
on the off stump line, jabbed to the off side
full and straight, Misbah opens the bat-face and guides it to backward point
on the off stump line, worked to right of midwicket
driven to long-on and Misbah runs the first run hard and comes back for the second
length delivery, outside off and Afridi cuts hard but straight to point
punched to long-on, they think about the second run but the throw comes in quick and accurate
from over the wickets, outside leg stump, flicked past square leg
lands on the leg stump, turns towards off, Afridi defends cautiously to the off side
on the back foot, driven to right of long on
down the leg side
moves outside leg stump and drives a full delivery to long-off
innovation. Misbah plays the reverse sweep and sends the ball racing to the point boundary
goes back to push to midwicket
full in length, outside off and Afridi drives to right of deep cover
See the ball, hit the ball. Afridi reckons its a simple game. He took the front foot out of the line and swung the full delivery over wide long-on
driven to wide long-off for two runs
short in length, outside off and Afridi cuts to right of wide third man
driven to long-off for a single
The white ball is flying everywhere. What a way to bring up his fifty. Afridi is on a roll. Another fullish delivery has disappeared over long-on. One clean swing of the bat and it sails into the sky
on the middle stump line and reverse swept to short thirdman region
comes down the track and drives to long-on.
turned to backward square leg.
comes out, takes it on the full and drives to right of long-on
lands outside legstump, worked to backward square leg
moves outside leg stump, the bowler follows him and Afridi whips it to long-on
sweeps to the fine leg boundary and the runs continue to flow
driven to covers
slightly short and cut past cover
Afridi is unstoppable. He just wrists a low full toss brutally over midwicket
full in length, driven to long-on for a single
picks up a single with a drive to long-off
flicked away to deep midwicket for two runs
another single, this time with a drive to long-on
A six over extra cover. Afridi continues to dazzle. It was flighted on the leg stump line but Afridi makes room by going down leg side and drove it inside-out over extra cover. Stunning hit.
charges down the track and swings it furiously over long-on. What a player. The crowd simply love it. With Gilchrist retiring soon, these Afridi innings make for great viewing.
on the middle stump line, flicked behind square leg for a single
threatens to jump out but Price pushes it through and Afridi pushes it back down teh track
on the off stump line, goes back to punch it to long-on for a single
moves outside leg stump and drives to long-on for another single
nice variation from Price. He really slows up the pace and Misbah is forced to wait and he defends in the end.
well outside off stump, full in length, Afridi goes for a swipe across the line and edges it past the 'keeper
full in length, driven to long-off
Afridi is gone. Big wicket. He walked across the stumps, went for a swipe across the line but got a thick edge over covers where Mazakadza ran behind to hold a neat catch
full pitched outside off and Misbah square drives it to deep point
flicked past square leg
pushed back to the bowler
worked to the on side for a single
floats in with the arm, tickled to square leg
on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
this time, pushed to covers
from over the wickets, floated in the middle and leg, Misbah leaned forward to drive to long on
swept to short fine leg
on the off stump line, driven to covers
wide down the leg side
turned to midwicket
outside the leg stump and its swept to square leg
wristed to short fine-leg for a single
on the stumps, swept to long leg for a single
on the leg stump line, flicked to square leg for a single
moves outside leg stump and misses a cut shot. The ball landed outside leg and spun between him and the leg stump
pushed to mid-off
Leans forward to drive to mid-off
driven to long-off for a single
down the leg side and a wide is called
outside leg stump and is swept to short fine leg
he is bowling from over the wickets and just outside leg stump. So Akmal charges outside leg stump and drives it over the bowler's head
he continues to reverse sweep at regular intervals. This one landed outside leg stump and is wished away to deep point region
turns in from outside leg and is swept to short fine leg
And the reverse sweep goes awry this time. You can't win with that shot all the time. It was full and on the middle and leg, Misbah went for his reverse sweep but edged it straight to backward point.
on the stumps and Kamran Hussain picks up his first international run with a sweep to long leg
on the middle and leg, tickled to short fine leg
his second run too comes via a sweep shot
pushed to extra cover for a single
short of length, outside off stump, Akmal punches it to left of long-off
pushed to point region for a single
full in length, shapes in a touch and Hussain drives to right of long-on for a single
on a length, on the middle and off and Akmal jabs it back to the bowler
hits a length delivery on the up to long-off for a single
short in length and Hussain pulls it away for a single
picks up a single with a on drive to midwicket
tossed outside leg, swept to right of short fine leg
goes back to turn a full delivery to left of short fine leg
Low full toss and Akmal choses to reverse sweep it past point
flighted delivery, driven to long-off for a single
turned to short fine leg
full and straight, Akmal goes down on his knee and swings it away to long-on but the placement is not right and he is restricted to a single
fuller, a tad slower and Hussain drives inside-out to right of sweeper cover
on the stumps and Hussain pulls it for a single
slightly short and Akmal cuts to right of deep backward point
another swing and gets a top edge but it lands safely behind the midwicket fielder and well ahead of the deep midwicket fielder.
dropped by Sibanda. He charged down the track and heaved to right of long-on where Sibanda tried gamely with a dive to his right but couldn't hold on. Good try.
short and outside off, cut away to wide third man
flighted up and Akmal swings it inside-out over extra cover
change of pace but the length is too short and Akmal pulls it away to deep midwicket boundary
dropped by Taibu. Akmal gets a edge, trying to late cut and Taibu couldn't hold on
goes for a slog but ends up inside-edging it to the pads
Caught in the deep. It was a short-of-length delivery, a touch slower too and Akmal pulls it in the air to deep midwicket
gets off the strike with a drive to long-off
fullish, driven to mid-on
full in length and driven to long-on
goes past covers for two more runs
fullish and is driven to long on
sails down the leg side
hmm ... he repeats that mistake
full pitched and heaved straight to long-on
short of length and Hussain swivels to pull it away to the fine-leg boundary
they add a run, courtesy a leg bye and so, the target is 273.

inn2.comm: full and on the stumps, turned to square leg.
full again and its on driven through midwicket
full and outside the off stump, left alone
leans forward, opens the bat-face and pushes to point for a single
full in length, beaten on the drive outside off stump
lets this one fly past the off stump
length delivery and is pushed back down the track
shapes in and is worked towards square leg for a single
shout for lbw. It landed on the middle stump and cut in, and he is beaten on the drive and is struck on the pad. Close call there.
full and outside off ,square driven through point
on the stumps, pushed to extra cover
Pakistan strike early. It landed full in length, outside off stump and he went for a drive and nicked it behind.
slides down the leg side, wide called
runs off the pads to fine leg
beaten outside off stump. It curved away from Masakadza who shapes to drive and checks his shot at the last minute
length delivery around the off stump and is worked to point
fuller in length, opens the bat-face and guides to backward point
quite similar to the previous two deliveries and the result is the same: no run
well outside the off stump and its a wide
nice probing delivery outside off stump and he pushes at it and is beaten
short of length, on the middle stump line, turned to the leg side
pushed back to the bowler
beaten again. Fuller and again it moves away from the batsman who ends up playing a loose drive
another that slants away and he shapes to play at it before withdrawing his bat
driven to covers
Full and the testing line outside off stump continues. Another play and a miss
more trouble for the batsmen around the off stump. It lands on a length, on the middle and off and teases the outside edge
more harassment. Again on that outside-off line, another play and a miss
three times in a row. This one lands on a length and shapes past the outside edge.
cracker. Tanvir gets this one to bend back in and Masakadza offers no shot but this one climbs high and strikes him on thigh pad
full and on the leg stump line, wristed past square leg
In the zone outside off stump, swings away and Williams covers his off stump before shouldering arms
back to regular programming. Yep, beaten outside off. Fuller and Williams is sucked into a loose drive before the ball moved past the bat
Hmm ... the torment continues. Again full and shaping away and again Williams is beaten on the drive.
on the middle and leg, Williams tries to turn it to the on side but the late movement means it ran off the outer edge to cover point
huge shout for lbw and again that was close. It curved in from the off and middle, and Masakadza was beaten on the drive and was struck in front of the stumps before hitting the bat.
runs it down to third man for a single
walks down the track and Tanvir pushes it down leg side
pushed towards mid-off for a single
full and straight, defended on the front foot
fullish and driven to covers
full and outside off, shapes to square drive and it runs to third man off the outside edge
breaks free with a drilled boundary through extra cover
on a length, around the off stump, guided to point
leans forward to defend to covers
driven to covers
short of length, comes in to evade the intended glance and strikes the thigh pad
full and straight, pushed down the track

And finally the ball collides with the outside edge. Masakadza stabbed at a length delivery leaving him and the edge took the ball low to Younis Khan, standing at a slightly wide first slip, and he pouches it safely, inches above the ground
beaten straightaway. It drew the batsman forward before leaving him
full in length, on the middle stump line, pushed down the wicket
fab extra cover drive. It was full in length, angling away from Taibu who drives it pleasingly through the off side.
shout for lbw as Taibu offered no stroke to a delivery that bent back in. But he was saved by the height there; it would have gone over the stumps
angling away and left alone.
short and wide, Taibu lashed at it and will pick up a boundary to the point fence
full and outside off, Taibu tried to whip it to the on side and gets a leading edge, along the ground, to mid-off
plants his left foot out, covers the off stump and shoulders arms to a delivery going in the channel
on driven towards mid-on
full and outside off, left alone
on the off stump line, pushed to cover point
edged but falls short of the slip fielder. It was on a length, outside off stump and he jabbed at it
drifts down the leg side
on the off stump line, pushed to covers
full in length, outside off stump and Williams square drove on the up through cover point
on a length, outside off stump, pushed back to the bowler
a touch short in length and Williams cuts past the diving point fielder
on the hips, tucked to square leg
strikes him on the pad outside off stump and it rolls away to the off side
from round the wickets, dabbed to the off side
from wide of the crease, from round the stumps, he angles it in and Taibu wrists it to left of long leg for two runs
length delivery on the stumps, punched to covers
length delivery, cut to point
full and outside off, driven to mid-off
driven to covers
whack. It was full and wide outside off and Williams freed his arms to carve it away over backward point
on a length, pushed to covers
taps close on the off side, want a run but changes mind as he sees the bowler move towards his right to make the stop
length delivery on the stumps, defended to the off side

Full and outside off stump, Taibu square drove it to right of Arafat at wide third man but made the wrong decision to turn back for the second run. The throw was fast and accurate and at the base of the stumps. Akmal collected and broke the stumps in one clean motion and Taibu, despite his dive, couldn't make it in time.
full and outside off stump, left alone. That was a needless run from Taibu
leans forward and defends solidly to covers
full and outside off stump, slashed to third man
pushed to the off side
pushed to deep cover for a single
on a length, around off stump, defended to covers
length delivery on the stumps, defended to the off side
fullish, on driven to left of deep midwicket for 2 runs
just outside off, steered to backward point
on the middle stump, tucked to square leg

leans forward to push a full delivery back to the bowler who fires in a throw at the striker's end and the batsman dives back to his crease. The throw missed the stumps though. Not that it would have mattered.
on the off stump line, pushed to cover point for a single
outside off stump, stabs at it and it runs to fine third man
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
on the off stump line, worked to backward point
pushed to mid-off
on a length, slanting across and is guided to wide third man for a single
on the stumps, worked to midwicket
